ce:section.ce:para:
The performances of the MIP@MPC@N-GQDs@Fe3O4
                        NH2 adsorbent were compared with the performances of a C18-pack SPE cartridge. Both adsorbents achieved extraction recoveries above 80 % (Fig. S9). Nevertheless, the developed adsorbent was simpler to use than the SPE cartridge, which required a manifold system, and the fabricated adsorbent can be reused for up to 6 cycles. To highlight the effectiveness of the developed method, it was compared with previously reported methods for the determination of THs (Table 3
                        ). The LODs, recovery and RSDs were better than or comparable to those of some other works. Moreover, the developed adsorbent was highly selective for THs, enabling its application in a variety of matrix samples. It also offers a more accessible approach for the extraction and determination of THs. These results confirm that the developed method can be used of extracting and determining THs in complex samples.
